`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- **Two-level idempotency**: Change detection happens at the preview layer (`stagedDiffersFromMR` → `collectTargets`), so `handleBatchPreviewConfirmed` only dispatches writes for MRs that actually differ. Within each write, `SaveApprovers` is further skipped if the approver set is unchanged — same pattern as the single-MR editor.
- **Closure snapshot discipline**: `makeBatchWriteCmd` captures `origApprovers` and `snapped` at call time (before any goroutine runs), preventing data races where model state could change between when the user confirms and when the API call resolves.
- **Result reuse**: Returning `ReviewersSavedMsg` from batch writes reuses the entire single-MR success path — in-place board update, "Reviewers saved" toast, and optional Teams notification — at zero additional handler code.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`

mrr-qtk.4 is complete. `handleBatchPreviewConfirmed` now dispatches one `makeBatchWriteCmd` per confirmed target (skipping writes when there are 0 targets), and each cmd mirrors the single-MR save logic: resolve user IDs via `GetProjectMembers`, call `SetReviewers`, conditionally call `SaveApprovers`, then `FetchMR` → `ReviewersSavedMsg`. All quality gates pass and the full E→editor→preview→confirm/back navigation is verified in agent-tui.
